---
alwaysApply: true
---

Suggest using specialized subagents when appropriate (do not auto-run them).

Only suggest once per issue unless new evidence appears (new stack trace, new failing test output, new repro step, or new code changes).

Token-safety / anti-loop guardrails:
- Do not propose repeated cycles by default. Make one best attempt, then stop.
- Never suggest re-running tests more than once without new code changes.
- Ask for confirmation before any additional debugging iterations, additional test runs, or expanding test scope.

Subagent suggestion routing:

- Suggest `debugger` when the user message includes crashes, stack traces, runtime exceptions, or build/runtime errors (e.g., "error:", "fatal", "crash", "stack trace", "SIGABRT", "Thread", Swift runtime exceptions).
- Suggest `test-runner` when code changes are made, or when there is test/build output (e.g., "XCTest", "Test Suite", "FAILED", "xcodebuild", failing assertions).
- Suggest `verifier` when work is claimed complete and needs validation.
- Suggest `security-auditor` when implementing auth, payments, or handling sensitive data.

Project schemes (replace placeholders in your app repo):
- "{{IOS_SCHEME}}"
- "{{WATCH_SCHEME}}" (optional)

When suggesting tests, prefer a copy/pasteable plan:
- Run tests for the relevant scheme(s) based on what changed.
- Report pass/fail counts and a short failure summary.
